Well I got it off, finally. The bolt was missing so that reduced a little bit of the effort needed to finish the task. I had been soaking it for a week and couldn't get it to budge. I smacked it a few times with a hammer to try and loosen it up. I then placed the handle of my pickle fork into the end of the rod where the shifter sits and gave it a few whacks. After about three good smacks it came right off! I just needed 
